      "example": "\n    <h3>Informationally Robust Auction Example</h3>\n    <p>A seller knows the common value \\(v\\) is distributed according to \\(F\\), but not what bidders know about \\(v\\). A mechanism \\(M\\) is evaluated by its worst-case equilibrium revenue:</p>\n    <div class=\"math\">\n      \\[\n        \\underline R(M)\n        =\n        \\inf_{\\pi\\in\\Pi}\n        \\inf_{\\sigma\\in BNE(M,\\pi)}\n        \\mathbb E_{\\pi,\\sigma}[t(b)].\n      \\]\n    </div>\n    <p>The robust design problem is</p>\n    <div class=\"math\">\n      \\[\n        \\sup_M \\underline R(M).\n      \\]\n    </div>\n    <p>The mathematical trick is usually to write the primal problem over Bayes-correlated outcomes and then use a dual solution to certify that a simple auction attains the best guarantee.</p>\n  ",
